---
import '../styles/global.css';
---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Info — allai.design</title>
  <meta name="description" content="About allai.design — curated AI product UI, design patterns, and tools for designers building with AI." />
  <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
</head>
<body>

  <header class="site-header">
    <div class="header-inner">
      <a href="/" class="site-logo">allai<span>.design</span></a>
      <nav class="header-nav">
        <a href="/" class="nav-link">Feed</a>
        <a href="/info" class="nav-link nav-link--active">Info</a>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main class="info-page">

    <section class="info-section">
      <h1 class="info-title">What is this</h1>
      <p>allai.design is a curated resource at the intersection of AI and design. Not another aggregator. Not a paywalled playbook. A place where designers get the signal without the noise — picked and framed by someone who actually ships AI products.</p>
      <p>The gap this fills: <a href="https://recent.design" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">recent.design</a> has great taste but ignores AI. <a href="https://aiverse.design" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">aiverse.design</a> has great AI coverage but it's paywalled and skews academic. allai.design sits in the open middle: free, opinionated, and growing.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="info-section">
      <h2 class="info-heading">What you'll find here</h2>
      <ul class="info-list">
        <li><strong>Visual curation</strong> — AI-generated interfaces, AI product UI, generative design outputs. Filtered hard — only what's actually worth seeing.</li>
        <li><strong>AI design patterns</strong> — How real products handle streaming text, error states, confidence indicators, prompt inputs, and more.</li>
        <li><strong>Articles</strong> — Curated links to the best writing on AI design and product thinking. Always a reason, never a link dump.</li>
        <li><strong>Tools</strong> — AI tools for designers with a short verdict: must-have / worth trying / not yet.</li>
        <li><strong>Product teardowns</strong> — Longer-form breakdowns of one AI product's design decisions per issue.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="info-section">
      <h2 class="info-heading">Who made it</h2>
      <p>Oykun Yilmaz — principal-level product designer with 25+ years of experience, currently Design Lead for Data and AI Experiences at a large bank. Also runs <a href="https://designermindset.net" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Designer Mindset</a>, a community and education business for designers.</p>
      <p>allai.design is top-of-funnel for Designer Mindset. The progression: discover allai.design → subscribe to newsletter → follow on X → join the community.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="info-section">
      <h2 class="info-heading">Tech stack</h2>
      <ul class="info-stack">
        <li>
          <span class="stack-name">Framework</span>
          <span class="stack-value"><a href="https://astro.build" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Astro</a> v4 — static site generation, zero JS by default</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="stack-name">CMS</span>
          <span class="stack-value"><a href="https://notion.so" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Notion</a> — content queue managed as a database, fetched at build time via the official API</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="stack-name">Hosting</span>
          <span class="stack-value">TBD — Vercel or Cloudflare Pages</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="stack-name">Newsletter</span>
          <span class="stack-value">TBD — Kit (formerly ConvertKit) or Ghost</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="stack-name">Styling</span>
          <span class="stack-value">Vanilla CSS — no framework, no utility classes</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

  </main>

</body>
</html>

<style>
.info-page {
  padding: 64px 24px 120px;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 56px;
}

.info-title {
  font-weight: 600;
  letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  margin-bottom: 20px;
}

.info-heading {
  font-weight: 600;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  color: var(--text-muted);
  margin-bottom: 16px;
}

.info-section p {
  color: var(--text-primary);
  line-height: 1.7;
  margin-bottom: 12px;
}

.info-section p:last-child {
  margin-bottom: 0;
}

.info-section a {
  text-decoration: underline;
  text-underline-offset: 3px;
}

.info-list {
  list-style: none;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 12px;
}

.info-list li {
  color: var(--text-primary);
  line-height: 1.6;
  padding-left: 16px;
  position: relative;
}

.info-list li::before {
  content: '—';
  position: absolute;
  left: 0;
  color: var(--text-muted);
}

.info-stack {
  list-style: none;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
}

.info-stack li {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 100px 1fr;
  gap: 24px;
  padding: 14px 0;
  border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  line-height: 1.5;
}

.info-stack li:last-child {
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
}

.stack-name {
  color: var(--text-muted);
}

.stack-value a {
  text-decoration: underline;
  text-underline-offset: 3px;
}

@media (max-width: 640px) {
  .info-page { padding: 40px 16px 80px; }
  .info-stack li { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 4px; }
}
</style>
